The House Committee on Rules offers the following substitute to HR 885:
A RESOLUTION
1 Creating the House Study Committee on Election Procedures; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the elective franchise is the cornerstone of our representative government; and
3 WHEREAS, Article II, Section I, Paragraph I of the Constitution provides that elections in
4 Georgia shall be conducted in accordance with procedures provided by law; and
5 WHEREAS, over the years Georgia election laws have divided responsibility for
6 administering and overseeing elections to a variety of state-wide and local officials and
7 boards, including but not limited to the Secretary of State, the State Election Board, and local
8 election superintendents and registrars; and
9 WHEREAS, while certain provisions of the Georgia Election Code, Chapter 2 of Title 21 of
10 the O.C.G.A., have been updated and modernized in recent years, other provisions have
11 remained unchanged since the original adoption of the state-wide Election Code in 1964; and
12 WHEREAS, further study and evaluation of the laws, policies, and procedures utilized in
13 administering Georgia elections is warranted; and
- 1 -

