14 WHEREAS, the state has a compelling governmental interest in ensuring that Georgia has
15 the most secure and effective electoral system in the nation.
16 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES:
17 (1) Creation of House study committee. There is created the House Study Committee
18 on Election Procedures.
19 (2) Members and officers. The committee shall be composed of a number of members
20 of the House of Representatives as determined and appointed by the Speaker of the House
21 of Representatives. The Speaker shall designate the chairperson of the House Committee
22 on Governmental Affairs as chairperson of the committee.
23 (3) Powers and duties. The committee shall undertake a study of the conditions, needs,
24 issues, and problems mentioned above or related thereto and recommend any action or
25 legislation which the committee deems necessary or appropriate.
26 (4) Meetings. The chairperson shall call all meetings of the committee; provided,
27 however, that the Speaker of the House of Representatives may set a maximum number
28 of meetings that the committee may conduct. The committee may conduct such meetings
29 at such places and at such times as it may deem necessary or convenient to enable it to
30 exercise fully and effectively its powers, perform its duties, and accomplish the objectives
31 and purposes of this resolution.
32 (5) Allowances and funding. The legislative members of the committee shall receive
33 the allowances provided for in Code Section 28-1-8 of the Official Code of Georgia
34 Annotated. The allowances authorized by this resolution shall not be received by any
35 member of the committee for more than three days unless additional days are authorized.
36 Funds necessary to carry out the provisions of this resolution shall come from funds
37 appropriated to the House of Representatives.
